  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2935",
  "title": "fix(clear-all): apply excludeAttribute correctly with clearsQuery",
  "body": "## Initial bug\r\n\r\nWhen clearsQuery and excludeAttributes are used together, we can clear the excluded attributes when the query is not empty\r\n\r\n## Reproducing the issue with the current InstantSearch\r\n\r\nhttp://extra-small-group.surge.sh\r\n\r\n - select a brand (note that the clearall button does not activate)\r\n - add some text in the search box (clear all button is activable)\r\n - click clear all\r\n - the query AND the brand are cleared\r\n\r\nbrand should not be cleared.\r\n\r\n## Notes \r\n\r\nThe problem is that fixing only this initial bug had an impact on `currentRefinedValues`. Both widget use the same utility function to provide the clear all feature but they have two opposite list system for excluding attributes: one is a white list, and the other a black list.\r\n\r\nThis patch refactors the utilities, baking the support of the two types of list in a single place. \r\n\r\nA next step for this could be to use a single connnector for current refined values and clear all widgets.",
